The Omu-Aran Development Association (ODA), has felicitated with one of its illustrious sons, Bishop David Oyedepo, the General Overseer of Living Faith Church Worldwide, on the occasion of the church’s 40th year anniversary.  A statement on Sunday by the ODA Spokesman, Olayinka Owolewa, described Bishop Oyedepo as a man of God with an immaculate character. The statement also described the clergyman as a community leader per excellence, whose love for Omu-Aran development is unquantifiable. “Bishop Oyedepo is a world-class preacher, renowned writer, speaker and motivator of the new generation. “He has undertaken a massive Africa Empowerment drive to raise African leaders to take up the challenge of imparting their Nations, Societies and environs positively. “On behalf of the Olomu of Omu-Aran, Oba Abdulraheem Oladele Adeoti, the Olomu-in-council and ODA, I will like to extend our warmest greetings and gratitude to God and His servant Bishop David Oyedepo on this occasion of the 40th Anniversary. “As you celebrate the 40th Anniversary milestones in the history of the Living Faith Church, aka Winners Chapel International, we cannot but be thankful to the Almighty God for his manifold blessings and for how far He has brought the ministry. “We pray that faith and zeal for God’s house will forever consume you and the entire member of your ministry. “The ODA believes that this 40th Anniversary has ushered the church into a new breakthrough era in the history of the Commission,” Owolewa said in the statement. The ODA recalled that the Church that started from a grass cathedral has grown into a worldwide ministry and has many people enjoying the spiritual warmth and word of faith that it offers. Through this prophetic Commission, Bishop Oyedepo seeks to empower people so that they can maximize their potential in God for the benefit of mankind.